AB  - We examine how sovereign wealth fund (SWF) investments affect target firms' cost of debt. Using a large sample across 39 countries from 2004 to 2019, and applying a difference-in-differences (DiD) approach, we find that the loan spread of target firms decreases after equity investment by SWFs. This result holds when we use alternative specifications, and address endogeneity issues. Moreover, the negative effect is more pronounced for borrowing firms with higher risk. We also show that SWFs help reduce the cost of debt when they have a strong connection with the lead banks.
